<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="145" type="variation">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="145">Variation.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="145">
The female exhibits variation in the degree of punctation on the marginal zones of T1, ranging from with denser punctures separated by 1-5 puncture diameters (typical form) to almost impunctate with a few tiny punctures (1 ♀, Sichuan, Mujiangping). Specimens from China have fewer hind wing hamuli (9-11 versus 11-12 in other studied specimens from India and Southeast Asia). Interesting specimens of a black form were collected in montane Yunnan (1 ♀, 3 ♂; Zhongdian, Xiaqiaotou, 1800 m). Unlike the typical form with red colourised T1-T4, these individuals have entirely black metasomas. Similar variation in coloration was also studied by us (unpublished data) in other 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Sphecodes" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Sphecodes" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="145" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="145">Sphecodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
